{{Infobox coat of arms | name = Coat of arms of Alba-Iulia | image = Actual Alba Iulia CoA.png | image_width = 200 | middle = | middle_width = | lesser = | lesser_width = | armiger = City Government | year_adopted = | shield = | crest = A seven tower [[mural crown]] with a black eagle | supporters = None | motto = None | other_elements = | earlier_versions = | use = On the City hall's and Local Council's documents }}
The '''coat of arms of the Municipality of [[Alba Iulia]]''' unites the traditional [[heraldry|heraldic]] symbols of the three Romanian Principalities: [[Wallachia]]'s golden eagle, [[Moldavia]]'s black [[aurochs]], and [[Transylvania]]'s two lions rampant (i.e. standing on their hind legs). In chief is a Romanian crown on a [[ermine (heraldry)|ermine]] field.
